@sebastian-nagel you're right, the intention was to have it like 

```
 if(args.containsKey(Nutch.ARG_LINKDB)){
    if(args.get(Nutch.ARG_LINKDB) != null) {
```

This was because the other commands in the REST API do not require the user to give the full path of the crawldb, segment, linkdb directories as they are all mapped through their corresponding crawlIDs. 
Hence, the args {} containing and key=linkdb with value=null would act as a flag indicating that the user wants to use the linkdb associated with this crawlId for indexing. 
Or else, if the value=<some path> then that would be used for the linkdb. 

If there is a better way to achieve this please suggest, my thought to do it this way was to keep the format of requests for the job endpoint consistent across different jobs.

